*Random* Whatever it is that you do, do it and enjoy it (career, hobbies, relationships, etc). But always evaluate and re-evaluate if the energy spent is worth it. What served you in one season may not serve you in another, and that’s OK. Just avoid the “rinse and repeat” cycle of living life because it’s familiar. Make sure you receive fair value for where you spend your time and energy! *End Transmission*

I won the 2023 NYC Marathon!🥇

I also experienced significant cramping, walked many times, stopped to stretch often, and missed my goal time by 50 minutes. 

I won the race because I remembered that the event wasn’t just 1 day. The NYC Marathon was many weeks long, with early mornings and long nights, with speed work and cross-training, physical therapy and ALL the recovery. Let’s not forget about the sacrifices including spending long hours training instead of with my beautiful family. That dedication, commitment, and consistency is what I’m proud of. That’s what makes me a champion. 

Would I have liked to perform better? Sure! That’s why I had a time goal - to have something to shoot for. That’s why I train - to increase the chances of hitting that goal and enjoying the experience, pain free. 

Does everything always go as planned? Of course not. Not in a marathon and not in life. But you can only control how you act and react, and I chose to keep moving (as slow as necessary), to finish the job. 

How did YOU do? Whether you crossed the finish line and still had energy to run another marathon, or you struggled to make it across (like me), let me inform you that you won the race long BEFORE it started.

I won the 2023 NYC Marathon! And you did too! Congratulations, champion!

40! 🎂 

God - I am humbled and grateful for the experiences of my life and the opportunity to still live it! Thank you! 

When I was younger, I never fully appreciated birthdays. To celebrate something that was “going to happen anyway” and that you achieve by just “staying alive” was weird to me. I blame my ignorance on my youth.

As I’m more seasoned now, I have a newfound appreciation for the complex simplicity of another 365. It’s more than a day, and it’s valued to many in different ways, but I find it to be a perfect reflection point on the miracle of our lives and existence. 

I have the most incredible wife and two beautiful children who make me happier than I’ve ever been. I love you, Lourdes, Samuel, y Havana. I’m healthy and I’m privileged to live my passion every day. 
I don’t have it all, yet I want for nothing. I’m in a state of peaceful happiness. 

123123 - a great friend told me that today’s date seems auspicious. I like the sound of that. It’s always been symbolic to me to have been born on the last day of the year; to have the completion of the calendar year also be the beginning of my new age. I can’t wait to live what’s to come!
